column5: Maybe someone gave it a bath in glow stick juice.
Saw this in the comments thread. http://muskie.outdoorsfirst.com/board/forums/thread-view.asp?tid=60773&DisplayType=nested&setCookie=1
Biologists are still scratching their heads according to local news here this morning, just when u think u have saw it all....
Some one else recently posted about catching a pike with similar features. Not sure what site it was on, but more local to Ontario.
I caught this Pike on the weekend out of Georgian Bay. It had a neon tongue and a little around the mouth.

I caught a pike this weekend with similar colouration, not as neon, but definitely blue approaching light green.  Something is definitely up...? is this just a normal occurance, or is there something causing this?
Male Bowfin have the exact same coloration during spawning, caught them in the channels and marsh at Long Point like that. Totally unrelated I'm sure , just saying.
